# Wiki MCP Cursor mount enforcement

## Why this exists

Cursor Agent chats do not always expose MCP tools to the model even when **`centex-program-wiki`** is configured. Program enforcement therefore uses **scripts + hooks + logs**, not “assume MCP works because Settings shows green.”

## Mandatory controls

1. **`sessionStart`** runs **`scripts/cursor-session-start-automation.sh`**, which invokes **`scripts/verify-wiki-mcp-cursor-mount.sh`** by default ( **`CURSOR_SESSION_START_CHECK_WIKI_MCP=0`** to skip ). Failures append to **`.cursor/hooks/logs/session-start-automation.log`** and **do not** block IDE startup unless **`CURSOR_SESSION_START_FAIL_ON_WIKI_MCP_BAD=1`** (local QA).

2. **`scripts/post-cursor-restart-verify.sh`** runs the same mount script before **`wiki-operating-healthcheck.sh`** unless **`VERIFY_POST_CURSOR_SKIP_WIKI_MCP_MOUNT=1`**.

3. When triaging “wiki MCP broken / empty **`wiki_spaces_list`**”, operators and agents run **`./scripts/verify-wiki-mcp-cursor-mount.sh`** first, then **`./scripts/merge-cursor-mcp-wiki-centex.sh`**, **`./scripts/ci-llm-wiki-bootstrap.sh`**, and **`./scripts/wiki-operating-healthcheck.sh`** per **wiki/README.md** section 4.

## Canonical prose

- **docs/OPERATOR_SESSION_START_AND_IDE_REALITY_SSOT.md** — section A (**`sessionStart`** automation)
- **wiki/README.md** — section 4 (Cursor MCP wiring + triage)

CI exercises JSON-only validation with **`config/cursor-mcp-wiki-mount-ci-fixture.json`** (**`WIKI_MCP_MOUNT_SKIP_CLI=1`**) in **`.github/workflows/cursor-policy-guard.yml`**.
